# LiBeDAW v0.1 Implementation Roadmap: Path to Tier-1

This staged execution plan outlines the critical path to resolving the architectural bottlenecks identified in the Tier-1 Comparative Report. The stages are ordered by technical dependency, ensuring foundational audio engine changes are completed before higher-level UI and workflow features are implemented.

---

## Phase 1: Core Audio Graph & Latency Foundation
*Objective: Remove hardcoded limitations and establish a professional timing foundation.*

### 1.1 Dynamic Insert & Return Tracks [DONE ✅]
- **Implementation:**
  - `TrackColumn` uses `juce::Viewport` for the clip area; mixer strip pinned at bottom via `computeMixerHeight()`.
  - `updateContentSize()` queries actual per-column mixer height (dynamic send-knob count) instead of hard-coded constant.
  - `OwnedArray<juce::Slider>` for dynamic Send knob creation; `removeSendKnob()` for deletion.
  - `FixedTrackColumn` right-click context menu → "Delete Return Track" with full engine-side atomic-swap deletion (no thread stop).
  - `onReturnRackDropped` / `onDeleteReturnTrack` wired end-to-end in `MainComponent`.
- **Validated:** Mixer strip stays pinned regardless of pattern count; return tracks can be created and removed cleanly.

### 1.2 Plugin Delay Compensation (PDC) [DONE ✅]
- **Implementation:**
  - `EffectProcessor` base class gains `virtual int getLatencySamples() const { return 0; }` — all existing effects are automatically PDC-transparent (zero latency).
  - `PdcDelayLine` struct: lock-free stereo ring-buffer delay (8192-sample max ≈ 170 ms @ 48 kHz), lives inside `Track`.
  - `Track` gains `std::atomic<int> pdcDelaySamples` + `PdcDelayLine pdcLine`.
  - `MainComponent::recalculatePDC()` — message-thread only: scans all effect chains for reported latency, computes `maxLatency`, writes per-track compensation into `pdcDelaySamples`/`pdcLine` atomically.
  - Render thread applies `pdcLine.process(trackScratch)` after the effect chain but before master accumulation — no thread stop, fully lock-free.
  - `recalculatePDC()` called automatically on `onEffectDropped` and `onDeleteTrack`.
- **Validated:** Zero-latency baseline builds and runs cleanly. Any effect overriding `getLatencySamples()` will automatically trigger correct per-track delay compensation.

---

## Phase 2: Advanced Routing & Mixing
*Objective: Enable professional mix-down capabilities.*

### 2.1 Sidechain Routing [DONE ✅]
- **Implementation:**
  - `Track` gained `std::atomic<int> sidechainSourceIndex` (-1 = disabled).
  - Render thread reads the sidechain source track's scratch buffer as a secondary signal, passed to `CompressorEffect` and `NoiseGateEffect` via `processWithSidechain()`.
  - `TrackHeader` right-click → "Set Sidechain Source" submenu lists all existing tracks; clears to -1 on "None".
  - `onSidechainSourceChanged` wired end-to-end in `MainComponent`.
  - `CompressorEffect` editor: full parameter controls (Threshold, Ratio, Attack, Release, Makeup, Mix) + real-time side-chain gain-reduction meter.
  - Sidechain source index saved/loaded per track in project XML.
- **Validated:** Kick drum successfully ducks a bassline. Attack/Release/Mix controls verified. Source persists across project save/load.

### 2.2 Group Tracks & VCA Faders [DONE ✅]
- **Implementation:**
  - `GroupColumn` class: inline Ableton-style folder track rendered in the scrollable grid at `SV_TRACK_W` wide. Features a fold/expand arrow (▶/▼), group colour stripe, child-count indicator, and volume fader.
  - `DisplayEntry` layout model in `TrackGridContent`: replaces implicit `i * SV_TRACK_W` positioning with an ordered list of `{isGroup, engineIdx, parentGroup}` entries. `resized()` iterates the list, hiding folded children with `setVisible(false)` and compacting scroll width automatically.
  - `groupBusIndex` atomic on `Track`: audio tracks write their summed output to the designated group scratch buffer instead of the master. Group scratch buffers accumulate through their own effect chains before the master mixdown.
  - `TrackHeader` right-click → "Assign to Group ▸" submenu: lists all existing groups + "New Group…". Selecting "New Group…" creates a group track on-the-fly and assigns immediately.
  - `GroupColumn` right-click: "Rename Group / Delete Group / Ungroup All".
  - `refreshGroupBadges()` syncs coloured pill badges on all audio track headers after any assignment change.
  - Effect drop on group columns: `itemDropped` hit-tests `groupCols[]` with `2000+i` index; `onEffectDropped` and `showDeviceEditorForTrack` both handle `>= 2000` range, routing to `groupTracks[g]`.
  - Fold state, group name, gain, and full effect chain saved/loaded per group in `<GroupTracks>` XML block.
- **Validated:** Multiple tracks assigned to a group; group folds and unfolds correctly; effects dropped on group bus appear in device panel; project save/load preserves all group state including fold state.

---

## Phase 3: Audio Manipulation & Arrangement
*Objective: Elastic audio and modern recording workflows.*

### 3.1 Real-Time Time-Stretching (Warping) ✅ DONE (2026-04-27)
- **Current State:** Audio clips play at their native speed.
- **Implementation:**
  - Integrated **Rubber Band Library v3.3.0** (R3 Phase Vocoder engine) via `FetchContent` + single-file amalgam CMake target.
  - Added `WarpMarker` struct and warp fields (`audioFilePath`, `clipBpm`, `warpEnabled`, `WarpMode`, `warpMarkers`) to `ArrangementClip` in `ClipData.h`.
  - New `AudioClipPlayer` class: lock-free decoder thread → input ring → RBL stretcher → output ring; `fillBlock()` never allocates or blocks.
  - `Track::clipPlayer` + `clipPlayerActive` atomic; render thread mixes stretched audio into `instrPool` additively.
  - `syncWarpRatiosToTempo()` called on every BPM change to update all active stretch ratios.
  - Full XML save/load of warp data (markers, clipBpm, warpEnabled, warpMode).
  - UI: orange **W** badge, yellow ◇ warp-marker diamonds on `ArrClipBlock`; right-click menu: Enable/Disable Warp, Set Clip BPM, Warp Mode (Complex active; Beats/Tones stubbed for v0.2 in `ideas_for_v0.2.md`).
- **Validation:** Change the global project tempo by +/- 20 BPM and verify that audio loops remain in sync without pitch artifacts.

### 3.2 Non-Destructive Comping & Crossfading ✅ DONE (2026-04-27)
- **Current State:** Basic recording via `AudioInputProcessor` and `RecordingThread`.
- **Implementation:**
  - New `Take` and `CompRegion` structs added to `ClipData.h`; `ArrangementClip` extended with `std::vector<Take> takes` and `std::vector<CompRegion> compRegions`.
  - Hard cap of **8 takes per clip** enforced in `registerNewTake()` (bounded by decoder-thread count).
  - New `CompPlayer` class (`CompPlayer.h/.cpp`): owns up to 8 `AudioClipPlayer` instances (one per take); pre-computed equal-power fade table (`cos(π/2·i/N)`); `fillBlock()` is lock-free, allocation-free; GC via `LockFreeQueue` pointer swap mirroring the `arrangementGarbageQueue` pattern.
  - `Track` gains `std::unique_ptr<CompPlayer> compPlayer` + `std::atomic<bool> compPlayerActive`; `timerCallback` polls `allPlayersLoaded()` and flips the flag once all background decoders are ready.
  - **Loop record:** `RenderThread` increments `std::atomic<int> loopWrapCounter` on every loop-wrap; `RecordingThread` polls the counter and atomically seals the current WAV + opens a new take file within the 20 ms poll cycle — no gap in audio capture.
  - `registerNewTake()` (message thread): appends Take, creates a default full-clip `CompRegion` for take 0, drops oldest when cap is hit; calls `loadCompPlayerForTrack()`.
  - **Comp region editing** (`onCompRegionSwiped`): splits/merges `CompRegion` list at snapped 1/16-bar boundaries; launches a background `juce::Thread` for zero-crossing search at each new boundary and writes back refined `fadeInSamples`/`fadeOutSamples` via `callAsync`.
  - **UI — `TakeLaneOverlay`**: lives inside `ArrangementContent` below the clip row (mirrors `ArrangementAutomationOverlay` pattern); teal fill = active region, waveform thumbnail via `juce::AudioThumbnail`, swipe gesture commits on `mouseUp`. Right-click on any clip block → "Show Take Lanes (N takes)".
  - Full XML save/load: `<Takes>` and `<CompRegions>` blocks nested inside `<ArrangementClip>` nodes.
  - Warp + comping mutually exclusive in v0.1 (comp path wins if `takes.size() > 0`); full integration design deferred to `ideas_for_v0.2.md`.
- **Validation:** Record 3 takes of audio in a loop, expand take lanes via right-click, swipe across different lanes to form a comp, verify seamless pop-free composite playback. Save/reload project and confirm all takes and comp regions are restored.

---

## Phase 4: Modern MIDI & Expression
*Objective: Future-proof synthesis and sequencing.*

### 4.1 MPE (MIDI Polyphonic Expression) Integration ✅ DONE (2026-04-27)
- **Previous State:** Standard 14-bit MIDI only; all notes shared a single pitch-bend lane; no per-note pressure or timbre routing.
- **Implementation:**
  - **`TrackCommand`**: added `MpeExpression` to the `Type` enum and a `MpePayload` POD struct (noteId, channel, pitchBendSemitones, pressure, timbre) as a zero-initialised member. `static_assert(is_trivially_copyable_v<TrackCommand>)` enforces ABI for `LockFreeQueue<TrackCommand,128>`.
  - **`MidiNote`** (`ClipData.h`): extended with `hasMpe`, `pressure`, `pitchBend`, `timbre` snapshot fields; defaults preserve full backward compatibility with all existing projects.
  - **New `MpeZoneManager`** (`Source/Core/MpeZoneManager.h`): message-thread-only class. Detects lower/upper MPE zones from RPN 0 / CC#6 messages *or* by auto-detecting simultaneous multi-channel Note Ons (permissive fallback for controllers that skip RPN). Tracks per-channel note assignments and translates PitchBend / ChannelPressure / CC74 into `TrackCommand::MpePayload`.
  - **`MainComponent`**: `mpeZone` member (message thread only) + `std::atomic<int> mpeTargetTrack{0}` (the currently selected/armed track receives live MPE). `handleIncomingMidiMessage` routes expression CCs through `mpeZone` → `commandQueue`; Note On/Off still forwarded to `midiCollector` for voice allocation.
  - **`Track::processPatternCommands`**: new `MpeExpression` branch translates payload into `juce::MidiMessage::pitchWheel` + `channelPressureChange` + `controllerEvent(74)` injected into `midiBuffer` at sample offset 0 — no heap allocation, no new thread.
  - **`WavetableSynthProcessor` / `WTVoice`**: per-voice `mpeChannel`, `mpePitchBendSemitones`, `mpePressure`, `mpeTimbre` fields; `noteOn(ch)` records the MPE channel and resets expression. `renderNextBlock` applies `bendRatio = pow(2, semitones/12)` to `baseFreq`, scales amplitude by `mpePressure` (or routes to filter cutoff), and offsets wavetable position by `mpeTimbre`. `processBlock` dispatches `isPitchWheel` / `isChannelPressure` / `isController(74)` to the matching voice by channel. `WTParams` gains `mpePressureTarget`, `mpeTimbreDepth`, `mpeBendRange` atomics (saved/loaded in `ValueTree`).
  - **`FMSynthProcessor` / `FMVoice`**: identical MPE voice-state pattern; `renderNextBlock` applies bend to `baseFreq` and pressure to output amplitude; `FMParams` gains `mpePressureTarget`, `mpeTimbreRange`, `mpeBendRange` atomics.
  - **GUI**: both `WavetableSynthComponent` and `FMSynthComponent` gain an **MPE MAPPING** panel: *Pressure →* ComboBox (Amplitude / Filter Cutoff) + *Timbre Depth* / *Bend Range* knobs (default ±48 semitones, GUI-adjustable).
  - **`PianoRollEditor`**: notes with `hasMpe == true` render in a **blue→red** gradient by pressure; a yellow **pitch-bend indicator** (line + dot) is drawn below the note block when `|pitchBend| > 0.05` semitones.
  - **XML persistence**: `WTParams` / `FMParams` MPE config saved as `mpePT` / `mpeTD` / `mpeBR` properties; `MidiNote` MPE fields deferred to the MIDI recording phase (v0.2); all existing presets and project files load without change.
  - Deferred to v0.2 (documented in `ideas_for_v0.2.md`): dedicated MPE Input Track selector (option B), real-time MIDI recording with per-note snapshot capture, manual "Set Expression…" right-click in the Piano Roll, and full FM operator-ratio timbre modulation.
- **Validation:** Build verified clean (zero errors). Manual test: connect an MPE controller (or virtual MIDI loopback), play simultaneous notes on different channels, verify per-note pitch bend on `WavetableSynth` and independent amplitude via pressure. Save/reload project; confirm MPE GUI knob values round-trip correctly.

---

## Phase 5: Hardware Control Surface API
*Objective: Full hardware integration with 2-way MIDI feedback and session navigation.*

### 5.1 Control Surface API Foundation ✅ DONE (2026-04-27)
- **Implementation:**
  - New `Source/ControlSurface/` subsystem. All existing code untouched — purely additive.
  - `ClipStateObserver.h`: `ClipState` enum (`Empty`, `HasClip`, `Queued`, `Playing`, `Recording`) + `LedColor` protocol-neutral integer constants + pure-virtual observer interface.
  - `ControlElement.h`: `ButtonElement` (Note On/CC bidirectional) and `SliderElement` (CC bidirectional) with `sendValue()` for hardware LED/motor feedback.
  - `ControlSurface.h`: Abstract base inheriting `ClipStateObserver`, declares `getDeviceName()` and `handleMidi()`. `setMidiOutput()` / `sendMidi()` convenience wiring.
  - `SessionComponent.h/.cpp`: NxM session ring with `trackOffset`/`sceneOffset`, `scrollTrack()` / `scrollScene()`, `setSlotButton()`, `lastKnownState` matrix (zero idle LED sends), and `resync()` for full LED rebuild on layout change.
  - `MixerComponent.h/.cpp`: per-track fader, mute, solo, arm button bindings forwarding to `MainComponent` callbacks.
  - `ControlSurfaceManager.h/.cpp`: owns all `ControlSurface` instances; `findOutputForSurface()` auto-detects MIDI Out by case-insensitive device name match; `handleMidi()` routes before MPE/note path; `notifyClipState()` / `notifyTransport()` / `notifyLayout()` broadcast state changes.
  - `MainComponent.h`: `#include "../ControlSurface/ControlSurfaceManager.h"` + `ControlSurfaceManager controlSurfaceManager` member.
  - `MainComponent.cpp`: 8 notify call-sites wired: MIDI guard at top of `handleIncomingMidiMessage`, Transport Play/Stop, `onLaunchClip`, `onPauseClip`, `onLaunchScene`, `onDeleteTrack`, `onInstrumentDropped`.
  - `CMakeLists.txt`: 3 new `.cpp` files + `Source/ControlSurface` include path.
- **Validated:** Build clean — zero errors, zero new warnings.

### 5.2 APC Mini Driver Implementation ✅ DONE (2026-04-27)
- **Implementation:**
  - New `Source/ControlSurface/ApcMiniDriver.h/.cpp` — concrete `ControlSurface` driver for the Akai APC Mini Mk1.
  - **Hardware protocol (Mk1):** 8×8 grid on Ch.1 notes 0–63; scene buttons notes 82–89; track select/arm buttons notes 64–71; Shift button note 98; faders CC 48–55 (tracks) + CC 56 (master). LED velocity: 0=Off, 1=Green, 2=GreenBlink, 3=Red, 4=RedBlink, 5=Yellow, 6=YellowBlink.
  - **`ApcMiniDriver`**: inherits `ControlSurface`; owns stack-allocated `std::array<std::array<ButtonElement,8>,8>` grid, 8 scene buttons, 8 track buttons, 1 shift button, and 9 `SliderElement` faders. Zero heap allocation in all hot paths.
  - **`stateToVelocity()`**: maps `ClipState` enum → APC Mini–specific velocity values (Empty=0, HasClip=Yellow=5, Playing=Green=1, Queued=GreenBlink=2, Recording=Red=3).
  - **`buildMapping()`**: wires all elements to `SessionComponent` and `MixerComponent` at construction time. Scene buttons call `csLaunchScene(absScene)`; track buttons select the track or stop the playing clip when Shift is held; faders CC 48–55 → track volumes, CC 56 → master volume.
  - **`handleMidi()`**: dispatch loop routes messages to shift button first (updates `shiftHeld`), then grid, then scene/track buttons, then faders. Returns `true` only on match — consumed messages never reach the note/MPE path.
  - **`fullSync()`**: iterates visible session ring (8×8 window from current offsets), calls `getClipState()` for each slot, and sends the correct LED velocity. Also blanks scene/track buttons. Called by `ControlSurfaceManager` after MIDI output is opened.
  - **`onClipStateChanged()`**: delegates to `SessionComponent` for ring-window translation, then overrides the LED send with the APC Mini–specific velocity (bypasses `defaultLedForState()`).
  - **Anti-feedback guarantee**: LED sends go via `midiOut`; DAW actions go via `cs*` proxy methods → `sessionView` callbacks → audio engine. Paths are fully separate.
  - **`MainComponent` public API additions**: `getClipState(t,s)`, `getNumTracks()`, `getNumScenes(t)` read-only accessors; 7 `cs*` proxy methods (`csLaunchClip`, `csLaunchScene`, `csPauseClip`, `csSelectTrack`, `csTrackArmChanged`, `csTrackVolumeChanged`, `csMasterVolumeChanged`) forward to existing `sessionView` lambdas with bounds-guarding.
  - **Registration**: `controlSurfaceManager.addSurface(make_unique<ApcMiniDriver>(*this))` at the end of `MainComponent::MainComponent()`. Auto-detect + `fullSync()` happen inside `addSurface()`.
  - **`CMakeLists.txt`**: `Source/ControlSurface/ApcMiniDriver.cpp` added to `target_sources`.
- **Validated:** Build clean — zero errors, zero new warnings (`cmake --build build -j$(nproc)` exit code 0).


### 5.3 Browser & Transport Navigation
- **Implementation:**
  - Create a `BrowserComponent` in the API to traverse the file/plugin tree via hardware directional buttons (e.g., using Shift + Arrows on the APC Mini).
  - Implement a hardware "Load" binding to instantiate the selected browser item onto the currently armed track.
  - Map global transport controls (Play, Stop, Record, Session/Arrangement toggle).

---

## Summary of Execution Strategy

To execute this roadmap efficiently without breaking the application, development should be strictly sequential. **Phase 1** requires deep brain surgery on the `RenderThread` and atomic track structures. Only once the lock-free dynamic effect chain is stable should the team proceed to **Phase 2** (Routing). **Phases 3, 4, and 5** are largely additive and can be developed in parallel once the core engine is finalized.
